  "texts": [
    "Dziugaite and Roy (2018) proved that any data-dependent prior can actually be used in Seeger's bound, under a differential privacy condition, at the cost of a small modification of the bound.",
    "Theorem 3.10 (Theorem 4.2, Dziugaite and Roy (2018)).",
    "Assume we have a function Π that maps any sample s = ((x 1, y 1),.",
    ", (x n, y n)) into a prior π = Π(S).",
    "Remind that the data is S = ((X 1, Y 1),."
  ]
